    "spellcaster": false,
    "monster": true,
    "notes": "100kg Undead, urban walker, #App: 2d6, Treasure: Small. Claws (1d6), Bite (2d6); armor 1; walks 10m/action; Morale +1. The ghoul is a predatory undead being, a walking, hungry, corpse. It seeks to feast on the flesh of the living and transform their victims into more ghouls. Undead: immune to poison, disease, and suffocation. Only takes half damage (rounded down) from non-silver, non-magical weapons. A character bitten by a ghoul must throw END 8+ or be paralyzed for 1d6 rounds. A creature slain by a ghoul will rise as a ghoul the following midnight, unless its body is cremated.",
